SubjectRegulations Amending and Repealing Certain Canadian Food Inspection Agency Regulations (Miscellaneous Program)
PrecisRegulations Amending and Repealing CERTAIN CANADIAN FOOD INSPECTION AGENCY REGULATIONS (MISCELLANEOUS PROGRAM) in order to (1) repeal obsolete or spent regulatory provisions which have no current application; (2) correct a discrepancy between the French and English versions; (3) harmonize the regulations with the enabling statute; (4) add clarity and consistency to regulatory provisions; (5) correct typographical or grammatical errors; (6) eliminate redundancies between regulations and the enabling Acts; and (7) correct or repeal provisions that are ultra vires.
